reviews.review: It was alright! Moments had me excited, but most of the time I found myself rolling my eyes.

(No spoilers) I very much enjoyed this movie. It’s easily better than the prequels and Episode 8. There’s one questionable scene for me, but as I writer, I think it was left in the script to make a moment that followed it that much more heartbreaking, so I’m good with it. Ignore the critics saying “it’s the worst Star Wars ever.” They’re ridiculous. It won’t make every fan happy (whatever does), but it’s a solid and enjoyable final chapter.
An unbalanced, Frankenstein of a film that spit in the face of The Last Jedi.

Boring,unoriginal,predictible,Rey....OMG Rey is soooo OVERPOWER she literally can do EVERYTHING without any training what so ever.This Movie is mind numbing and it's feels like you play an EASY mode in already easy video game.Totally trash.
They basically retold the same stories from the original trilogy and even the prequels plus through in stuff that was never mentioned in the first 2 or even hinted in the first 2.
The movie leaves intact the lessons of The Last Jedi while still evolving them and rhyming with Return of the Jedi in its own unique ways.

I was not disappointed.  I loved the film, and the big, emotional moments, small callbacks, and even the so-called fan service.  I'm a life-long fan, born in 1970, and I had so much fun watching this.  It is not a perfect movie by any means, but that is not my expectation.  I want to have fun, be wowed, maybe cry a little, feel nostalgic, meet new droids and aliens, and leave feeling exhilarated.  Plus, Adam Driver.  <3

After the Last Jedi, this movie tries to fix the inconsistencies. While there are some good moments, and the actors do their jobs pretty well, it is still a bad Star Wars Trilogy movie. As a stand-alone would have been ok maybe 3 stars, but this trilogy was ruined in The Last Jedi. JJ tried to fix things, but you cannot fix something that is already broken.

BEST STAR WARS MOVIE OUT THE NEW TRILOGY!!!!!!! I loved every single part of it. An amazing ending to such a remarkable story that was one that ABSOLUTELY needed to be told. Can’t get any better than this movie. 11/10
A total clusterf of writing , im glad its over.
